======================================================================
PART 7: CHARACTERISTIC POLYNOMIAL AND DISCRIMINANT
======================================================================
Q_1,...,Q_m are roots of a degree-m polynomial with integer coefficients.
prod Q_k = (-1)^m * constant term = e_m (the last ESF).
The DISCRIMINANT of this polynomial might have number-theoretic meaning.

  p=7 (Interval), m=3:
    Q_vals = ['5.048917', '0.307979', '0.643104']
    e_j = [6, 5, 1]
    prod Q_k = 1
    Discriminant = 49.0000 (rounded: 49)
    disc / p^2 = 1

